  "text": "It might be questioned whether it is possible to reduce the dose of cyclophosphamide. Ponticelli et al. [CITATION_1] have used cyclophosphamide in an alternating schedule, limiting the duration of cyclophosphamide therapy to 3 months. However, this short regimen has been studied extensively only in patients with normal renal function. We previously have reported a comparison of the Ponticelli regimen (with chlorambucil) and our 12 month cyclophosphamide regimen [CITATION_2] . We found the cyclophosphamide regimen more effective and less toxic than chlorambucil. It remains to be proved if these differences are related to the difference in duration of treatment or the type of agent. Future 2042 P. W. G. du Buf-Vereijken and J. F. M. Wetzels studies are needed to settle this issue; meanwhile, we favour the 12 month regimen in patients with renal insufficiency.",
  "correct_citation": {
